# **What?**

This project is to implement Sinch vendor’s Seamless verification. Seamless Verification verifies user phone number with the carrier without any user action therefore should reduce friction compared to otc verification

# **Why?**

The existing login flows email-otc or phone-otc has a friction point i.e. users have to wait for the code and submit it. Our assumption is that seamless verification will remove that friction and improve user growth

## **Goals**

* Implement a login agonistic verification method  
* Adopt this login flow for android and ios   
* Fallback to otc flow

## **Introduction**

The proposed design holds verification logic into RDP, alongside with other forms of verification. Won’t include risk client sdk’s as they are out of scope to this work as this design relies on identity to initiate verification.

## **Architecture (Sinch Configuration)**

Sinch Developer account should be configured to ([SINCH Q\&A](https://docs.google.com/document/d/1OxjFlNUHzPiQAkVowYL6gwEuSssFSyhVPi1cF8BLUcM/edit))

* Skip initiation callback  
* Skip verification callback  
* Change the TTL of verification id per needs  
* Change the TTL of target id per needs

## **Architecture (Changes to Existing Services)**

### **IOS**

Use Sinch SDK  (required as permissions and response states are managed)  
Before mounting the webview check if data is turned off or user denied the permissions needed  
Mount Webview with pre-checks (isDataOff, hasUserDeniedPermissions)  
Setup a bridge with webview, listen for targetUri and initiate the GET via sdk On successful verification/On Failed verification send message to webview

### **Identity-web**

Mounted webview will have context about native app like (isDataOff, isPermissionDenied)  
Email or phone submission include attribute excluding seamless based on device context  
A new loading button UI while native client is performing verification  
On successful verification, request seamless GuidedLogin, do GuidedLookup with attribute excluding seamless.  
Handle new GuidedTypes for seamless verification.  
Establish a bridge with native client and pass targetUri  
Use a configurable timeout on verification and request GuidedLookup with attribute excluding seamless  
On Failed verification, request GuidedLookup with attribute excluding seamless

### **Identity-BFF**

The lookup request evaluation will be 

* On phone submit payload will be GuidedRequest with phoneNumber or email  
* In case of email submit, known or unknown won’t matter   
* In case of phone submit,  known or unknown still matters  
* Create guided session  
* Check if eligible for phone verification and seamless verification  
* Make a request to RDP to send seamless verification request  
  * With sessionId, phoneNumber  
  * Use preferred channels as seamless  
  * And allowed channels as sms and seamless  ( we need to do this for some cases like email unknown )  
  * So that guided lookup doesn’t have to retry if voip check fails or Sinch request fails  
  * Guided session and response will be based on MFASendResponse channel used  
* There are cases we have when we don’t rdp to retry and simply fail  
* Fallback to RDP error here would be otc flows (single or multi channel)  
* Return targetUri and guidetype email\_seamless or phone\_seamless

The login request evaluation will be 

* On verification success payload will be GuidedLoginRequest with phoneNumber  
* Check if guided session validity  
* Check rdp session isMFAVerified  
* Continue logic similar to phone otc verified  
* On rdp check failure we throw an error, UI should retry phone submit and may choose to disable seamless

### **Interface IDS-FE to IDS-BFF:**

GuideContext: {  
  isSeamlessBlocked: Boolean  
}  
/guided/lookup/email body GuidedEmailLookupRequest extend with GuideContext

Seamless Response will include: 

guideType: email\_seamless  
GuidedMFAChannelInfo {  
	contact: targetUrl.  
	notificationType: seamless  
}

No change in /guided/login/email

/guided/lookup/phone body GuidedPhoneLookupRequest extend with GuidedContext

Seamless Response will include: 

guideType: phone\_seamless  
GuidedMFAChannelInfo {  
	contact: targetUrl.  
	notificationType: seamless  
}

/guided/login/phone unknown or multi account 

Seamless Response will include:   
guideType: phone\_seamless\_email or phone\_seamless\_email\_signup  or phone\_seamless\_email\_password or phone\_seamless\_email\_social

## **MileStones**

* RDP Sinch Client integration to support Verification Request and Status  
* RDP support seamless verification as a channel  
* RDP extend Send rpc with seamless channel  
* RDP extend IsMFAVerfied rpc with seamless integration  
* IDS RDP client changes to support seamless channel  
* IDS login changes to /guided/lookup and /guided/login endpoints  
* IDS signup changes to /signup/phone endpoints  
* IDS UI changes to login and signup flow  
* IOS, Android changes to integrate Sinch SDK and webview bridges

## **Service Level Objectives (SLO)**

### **External vs Internal**

New Risk-bff endpoint will have a external client  
Risk-Gateway interfaces already have identity-bff as a client

### **Latency**

Sinch latencies: Request P95 250ms, Status: 10ms P95

### **Expected QPS**

For Signup additional 2 QPS to RDP  
For Login additional QPS to IDS and RDP will be due to fallback in case of failures 

### **Failure**

* Timeout will be 5 sec for verification, if verification fails then user is wasted and also we’r billed for failure  
* On SDK failure to verify from network, webview will try current otc flows  
* On gateway failure to initiate verification, BE will fallback to current otc flow   
* On gateway failure to handle callback verification or session verification failure, BE will throw an error. FE can chose to handle this based on metrics observed

## **I18n/L10n**

* Handled at identity-web and identity-bff

## **Alternative Designs**

The alternative design would include

1) determine phone number from native client and perform verification via 2/3 before mounting webview  
   1) Unnecessary costs if user prefers password or if seamless should be disabled  
2) Native client receive phone number from bridge and initiate verification with sinch  
   1) A bit insecure and needs request allow callback   
   2) Rdp will have to create its session on callback  
   3) Rdp will not create a session on the start and have to rely on sinch id for communication  
   4) Work to implement a bff public interface  
   5) Ids is no longer a  control switch   
3) Native client receive phone number from bridge and initiate verification with risk-bff  
   1) Work to implement a bff public interface  
   2) Ids is no longer a  control switch   
4) Native Client receive email from bridge and initiate verification with risk-bff  
   1) Work to implement a bff public interface  
   2) Ids is no longer a  control switch   
   3) Risk-bff should query identity to fetch user phone number
